Reasoning: The paper deals with a downlink multi-user multiple-input-single-output (MISO) system with 1-bit quantization at the transmitter, which is a topic of interest in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also presents a new precoding technique to mitigate multi-user interference and quantization distortions, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). The use of linear programming for optimization is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with massive MIMO systems, which is a topic of interest in the field of multimedia communication (cs.MM).
